  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Repose Project for Tonj North and South</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The CGF funded project will Provide timely, safe, dignified, and accountable humanitarian assistance. The area is affected by intercommunal conflicts causing displacements and as a result, hunger as communities are not stable to farm their land and produce their own food.  In addition, the displacement has caused trauma and stress among women, children and elderly which was initially related to property left back, lack of food and poor sleeping and living conditions. The population displaced are  deprived of their food, livestock, NFIs and their living conditions have deteriorated which counts to  more than 18,000 internal displaced persons (IDPs) are  temporarily hosted at Mayom biong Primary school, Church and some hosted by their relatives of Gogrial East County. The overall psychological wellbeing of IDPs and host communities is affected due to this calamities.</narrative>
  </description>
